review:
Similar things have been said about The Haven so my points of difference would be to;

* Request a room that has a deck that opens out onto the pool, they're numbered 0001-0012. It's in the front block and from our room (0002) we were only 6 steps into the water, bliss! I'd read comments that whilst the front rooms were closer to breakfast etc they were noisier‚Ä¶. we didn't notice this at all.

* You're only a hop skip and a waddle to a delicious Japanese restaurant. Walk out of the Haven, turn left and it's about 150 metres on your left, Ryoshi. It looks average on the outside (hence why we walked past it for the first 4 days) but once inside it's devine and usually pretty packed. Like most things in Bali it's also really well priced, we had 2 bento boxes, with 2 Bintangs and 2 sprites for NZ/AU $37.
